<task id="015" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>LocalAttachmentSource — file input picker for local-disk uploads</title>
    <phase>Wave 1 — Engine + Wrappers + Sub-Components</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>014</dependencies>
    <blocks>020</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, fluent-ui</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Source-specific picker — small surface area; no architecture decisions; follows the framework contract established in 014. STANDARD covers it.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-07</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build `LocalAttachmentSource.tsx` at `subcomponents/sources/LocalAttachmentSource.tsx`. Wraps a hidden `<input type='file' multiple />` and a visible Fluent `<Button>` that triggers the file dialog. Selected files become `IAttachment` records with `source='local'` and `localFile: File`.

    File picker respects the MIME allow-list defined in the upcoming `docs/standards/COMMUNICATION-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md` (Wave 6 task 088). For Wave 1, accept all MIME types — Wave 6 wires the allow-list in. Document the TODO clearly with a comment referencing task 088.

    Local files are NOT uploaded at this step — they're held client-side until `engine.send()`, which posts them as multipart form data alongside the BFF `/api/communications/send` request. (Server then uploads to SPE + captures `driveItemId` per existing R2 path.)
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer comfortable with file input + Fluent v9 Button + multi-file selection patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `LocalAttachmentSource.tsx` compiles + lint-clean. Clicking the Add button opens the OS file picker; selecting files adds them to the AttachmentList via `onAdd(IAttachment[])` callback. No MIME filter applied (Wave 6 wires policy).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-07, local is one of 4 sources. Simplest of the four — just a file input wrapper.

      MIME allow-list comes in Wave 6 task 088 (`COMMUNICATION-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md` analog of `CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md`). For Wave 1, accept-all is acceptable since server-side enforcement still applies (per NFR-04 server caps).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/sources/LocalAttachmentSource.tsx (NEW)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/AttachmentList.tsx (UPDATE — wire local picker to Add button)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/index.ts (UPDATE — export LocalAttachmentSource)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 only — `Button`</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">One canonical local picker — replaces ad-hoc `&lt;input type='file'&gt;` usages in other surfaces (e.g., DocumentEmailWizard)</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-04">Cap enforcement happens in `AttachmentList` framework — this picker just emits new `IAttachment[]`</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No MIME filtering yet — Wave 6 task 088 wires `COMMUNICATION-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md`. Add a TODO comment with the reference.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
