      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/AttachmentList.types.ts</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Author `LocalAttachmentSource.tsx`:
      - Props: `{ onAdd: (attachments: IAttachment[]) =&gt; void; disabled?: boolean }`
      - Hidden file input + visible Button labeled "Add from device"
      - onChange handler: convert `FileList` to `IAttachment[]` with `id: crypto.randomUUID()`, `name: file.name`, `sizeBytes: file.size`, `mimeType: file.type`, `source: 'local'`, `localFile: file`
      - Reset input value after select (so same file can be added twice if needed)
      - TODO comment: `// Wave 6 task 088 will add MIME allow-list per COMMUNICATION-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md`</step>
    <step order="2">Wire into AttachmentList — when `attachmentSources` includes `{ kind: 'local' }`, render LocalAttachmentSource's button.</step>
    <step order="3">Update `EmailComposer/index.ts` — export `LocalAttachmentSource`.</step>
    <step order="4">Smoke test: click button, select 2 files, verify they appear in AttachmentList with correct sizes + source badge "Local".</step>
    <step order="5">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</step>
    <step order="6">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 015 ✅.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="write">LocalAttachmentSource.tsx</tool>
    <tool name="edit">AttachmentList.tsx wire-in, index.ts barrel</tool>
    <tool name="bash">npm run build + lint</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="file">EmailComposer/subcomponents/sources/LocalAttachmentSource.tsx (NEW)</output>
    <output type="file">EmailComposer/subcomponents/AttachmentList.tsx (UPDATED — local picker wired)</output>
    <output type="file">EmailComposer/index.ts (UPDATED)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`LocalAttachmentSource.tsx` compiles + lint-clean.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Button click opens OS file picker; selected files appear in AttachmentList with source badge "Local".</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`IAttachment.localFile` populated with the `File` object.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TODO comment references task 088 / `COMMUNICATION-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Disabled when caps reached (controlled by parent AttachmentList).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Local source is the simplest of the 4. The interesting question is upload-at-send-time vs upload-on-add. We choose upload-at-send-time because (a) cancel-after-pick is a common flow, (b) avoids orphan uploads to SPE, (c) matches the existing R2 server-side pattern.
  </notes>

